name: Matariki
summary: During Matariki, a significant cultural celebration, various events and festivities take place across Aotearoa New Zealand. To protect nocturnal insects during the festival's extended nights, individuals are urged to dim outdoor lighting. Music enthusiasts can enjoy curated playlists by Aotearoa artists for Matariki 2024. In the Northland region, visitors can explore cultural experiences and activities. Wellington City offers diverse entertainment options throughout the long weekend. The Tīwhas Matariki Spectacular showcases vibrant indigenous performances. Christchurch City Council presents Matariki Weekend at Riverside, featuring cultural events. Martyn Pepperell's "Mānawatia a Matariki" provides an educational perspective on the celebrations. 1News simplifies Matariki traditions for beginners, while the New Zealand Herald shares culinary insights with Uncle Pare's Matariki recipes. The Spinoff recommends captivating viewing options for the long weekend.

name: My Lady Jane
summary: My Lady Jane, a new fantasy-themed television series, has garnered mixed reviews. Some critics, such as The Guardian, praise its unique blend of Tudor history with magic animals, while others, like IGN, find its premise outlandish. Variety, however, commends its entertainment value and lack of adherence to historical accuracy. The Globe and Mail highlights the series' subversion of traditional "damsel in distress" tropes, delving into the real-life experiences of Lady Jane Grey. BBC.com provides an in-depth look at the historical figure behind the character, while Literary Hub offers a behind-the-scenes glimpse into the production. TIME explores the intersection of historical events and creative liberties taken by the series. Inews applauds its extravagant nature, while TheWrap addresses the question of its binge-ability. Overall, My Lady Jane seems to offer a diverse and engaging viewing experience, with critics emphasizing its entertainment value while acknowledging its departure from historical accuracy.

name: Judith Whelan
summary: Prominent Australian journalist and editor Judith Whelan has passed away at the age of 63 after a valiant battle with cancer. Whelan was widely respected and beloved within the industry, having held esteemed positions at the Sydney Morning Herald and ABC. Colleagues at both organizations have expressed profound sorrow and admiration for her unwavering commitment to journalism and mentorship of young reporters. In her role as editorial director at ABC, Whelan played a pivotal role in shaping the organization's editorial vision and was instrumental in fostering a culture of excellence. She was also a trailblazer for women in the media, inspiring and empowering countless individuals throughout her career. Whelan's legacy as a dedicated and influential figure within Australian journalism will continue to be celebrated and remembered.
